The paper proposes a framework that uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to analyze CT lung screenings and reduce false positives. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of CNNs indicates that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of mini-batch to overcome class-imbalance, which suggests that it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed framework using the LUNA16 challenge evaluation, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
